bsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-parastyle=&quot;paragraph&quot;&gt;cutting-edge&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-parastyle=&quot;paragraph&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;software technologies.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233

&lt;p&gt;STR is looking for a &lt;strong&gt;GNC Algorithms&lt;/strong&gt; expert to be part of a multidisciplinary team of researchers and engineers dedicated to developing cutting-edge technologies with significant and immediate impact on our national security. We believe that each employee has a unique set of skills, experiences, and perspectives that are essential to providing our customers with innovative solutions to difficult national security challenges. Our culture takes pride in developing impactful technologies through collaborative teamwork while maintaining the highest standards of craftsmanship and quality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a GNC Engineer with versatile skills in aerospace guidance, navigation and control systems technology. Areas of particular interest includes advanced filtering and estimation techniques, flight control system design, and/or aerospace systems modeling. A successful candidate will join a team of algorithm and software developers in a fast-paced and results-driven prototyping environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We encourage applicants who are proficient at programming in at least one high-level programming language (e.g. C/C++, Python and/or MATLAB) for building models and algorithmic technologies in support of system analysis and development. In our view, the development of these models and technologies is benefited by sound understanding and hands-on experience with implementing guidance and control systems hardware.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing advanced control system algorithms for aerospace applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing algorithms for sensor and system research and threat analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing and analyzing aerospace GNC systems, including both hardware and software&lt;/li&gt;
