&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;As a&amp;nbsp;Lead&amp;nbsp;Modeling and Simulation (M&amp;amp;S) Engineer,&amp;nbsp;you will lead teams working a portfolio of projects focused on advanced modelling and simulation (M&amp;amp;S) capabilities, including RF system development, capability implementation, and integration of emerging capabilities into M&amp;amp;S environments. A particular growth area is the development of real-time M&amp;amp;S capabilities paired with hardware-in-the-loop simulation in support of operational test and evaluation efforts.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;This position requires skills in performing and leading multi-disciplinary teams designing and analyzing complex systems and&amp;nbsp;representing&amp;nbsp;them in simulation. Strong technical, interpersonal, communication, and technical leadership skills are needed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
